<HEADLINE>
GROWTH OF MANUFACTURING PRODUCTION INDEX SETS RECORD LOW
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April  24 (CNA) 04/24/07  21:01:20 (By Elisa Kao)
</P>
<P>
The growth of Taiwan's manufacturing production index (MPI) and
its industrial production index (IPI) in the first quarter of
this year both registered five- year lows, according to
statistics released Tuesday by the Ministry of Economic Affairs
(MOEA).
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that the MPI grew 0.99 percent in the first
quarter over the same period of last year, while the IPI
registered a year-on-year growth of 0.89 percent in the first
three months.
</P>
<P>
The IPI stood at 143.51 in March, representing a slight growth of
0.12 percent over the same period of last year and a significant
increase of 24.06 percent over February.
</P>
<P>
The MPI stood at 148.18 in March, representing a year-on-year
growth of 0.62 percent and an increase of 25.31 percent over
February.
</P>
<P>
On the IPI in the first quarter, the production of the water,
electricity and fuel sector increased 3.01 percent over the same
period of last year, while that of the mining and construction
sectors decreased by 18.61 percent and 4.9 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the MPI in the January-March period, the production of
the information and electronics industry represented a year-on-
year growth of 2.47 percent, followed by that of the chemical
industry at 2.29 percent, while the production of the metal and
machinery sector, and the consumer product industry, decreased by
2.83 percent and 0.98 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Feng Tien-chi, deputy director-general of the MOEA's Statistics
Department, said the increase of MPI in the first quarter
reflected the stable growth of the country's manufacturing sector
after suffering recession last December.
</P>
